text: Nandnee, also spelleda as Nandani, is a village in the Solapur district in Pune division of Desh region of Maharashtra state in India. ==Demographics== According to the 2011 census Nandani total population is 1,590, of which 801 are males while 789 are females. Population of children with age 0-6 is 223 which makes up 14.03% of total population. Literacy rate of Nandani village was 67.96% compared to 82.34% of Maharashtra. In Nandani Male literacy stands at 81.42% while female literacy rate was 54.28%. ==Transport== Nandnee is located on National Highway 52 which connects Sangrur in Punjab to Ankola in Karnataka. ==References== ==External links== * Nandani village Category:Villages in Solapur district
